article.description: — Terry Nolan Jr. had a season-high 23 points as Bradley topped Southern Illinois 74-66 on Saturday.
article.headline: Nolan Jr. scores 23 to lead Bradley past S. Illinois 74-66
article.linkText: Nolan Jr. scores 23 to lead Bradley past S. Illinois 74-66
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- — Terry Nolan Jr. had a season-high 23 points as Bradley topped Southern Illinois 74-66 on Saturday. Elijah Childs had 15 points, 12 rebounds and three blocks for Bradley (10-10, 4-7 Missouri Valley Conference), which ended its six-game losing streak. Lance Jones had 15 points for the Salukis (8-7, 2-7). Steven Verplancken Jr. added 14 points. Kyler Filewich had nine rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
